  "body": "Under Windows, \"npx hardhat help\" will give \r\nError HH12: Trying to use a non-local installation of Hardhat, which is not supported.\r\nPlease install Hardhat locally using npm or Yarn, and try again.\r\n\r\ncaused by hardhat/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/core/execution-mode.ts\r\n\r\nthis comparison won't work as the file path is case insensitive under windows, \r\n....\r\n23      fs.realpathSync(resolvedPackageJson) === fs.realpathSync(thisPackageJson)\r\n...\r\nquick fix for windows only is change it to \r\n        return (fs.realpathSync(resolvedPackageJson).toLowerCase() === fs.realpathSync(thisPackageJson).toLowerCase());\r\na proper fix need to consider all OS.\r\n  ",
